SIMPLE: ingrateful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ingrateful
<hw>In"grate`ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ingratus</ets> ingrateful (pref. <ets>in-</ets> not +
<ets>gratus</ets> beloved, dear, grateful) + <ets>-ful</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ingrat</ets>. See <er>Grateful</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Ungrateful; thankless; unappreciative.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He proved extremely false and <qex>ingrateful</qex> to me.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unpleasing to the sense; distasteful;
offensive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He gives . . . no <qex>ingrateful</qex> food.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In"grate`ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>In"grate`ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingrately</ent>⟦br⟧
